Description: Simple clipboard manager for Linux (X11)
 ClipMan is a lightweight clipboard manager for Linux X11 that runs
 in the background, monitoring clipboard changes and maintaining a
 persistent history of copied items.
 .
 Features:
  - Automatic clipboard monitoring with configurable history size
  - Persistent storage of clipboard entries
  - Pin important items to keep them forever
  - GTK3-based GUI picker with search functionality
  - Command-line interface for full control
  - Systemd service for auto-start on login
